🧩 ADMIN DASHBOARD — TESTS SECTION
Structural Template Engine Specification v2.0

0️⃣ Core Principle
Tests = Structural Templates
Assignments = Execution Instances
A Test template:
    • Freezes question set
    • Freezes difficulty distribution
    • Freezes timing profile
    • Freezes phase configuration
    • Freezes marking scheme
    • Generates canonical identity
After first assignment → structure immutable.

1️⃣ NAVIGATION STRUCTURE
Tests
   ├── Create Test
   ├── Test Library
   ├── Template Analytics
   ├── Distribution Review
   └── Template Settings

2️⃣ TESTS → CREATE TEST
Step 1 — Question Pool Selection
Teacher applies filters:
    • Subject
    • Chapter
    • Difficulty
    • Tags
    • QuestionType
    • Academic Year
    • Unused / Used
    • Custom filters
System returns:
X total questions matched
Now teacher chooses:
Generate test with Y questions (Y ≤ X)

3️⃣ X → Y SELECTION MECHANISM
Teacher must select one of the following:

3.1 Deterministic Manual Selection
UI shows filtered list.
Teacher manually selects Y questions.
Use case:
    • Curated test
    • Specific concept emphasis
Store:
selectionMethod = "manual"

3.2 Statistical Selection Options
3.2.1 Shuffle + Slice
    • Shuffle X
    • Take first Y
selectionMethod = "shuffle_slice"

3.2.2 Offset + Limit (Slice)
    • Sorted list (e.g., by createdAt or difficulty)
    • Take from offset N to N+Y
selectionMethod = "offset_limit"
Useful for segmented tests.

3.2.3 Round Robin
If multiple subjects selected:
Distribute evenly across:
    • Subjects
    • Chapters
    • Difficulty
Algorithm:
For each category:
    pick 1 question cyclically
until Y reached
Ensures structural balance.
selectionMethod = "round_robin"

4️⃣ CANONICAL TEMPLATE ID (CRITICAL)
After Y questions finalized:
Sort question IDs ascending.
Generate canonical string:
hash = SHA256(concatenatedQuestionIds)
Store as:
canonicalId
Before saving template:
Check:
Does canonicalId already exist?
If yes:
Show teacher:
“Duplicate template detected. Existing template: TEST_023”
Teacher may:
    • Reuse existing template
    • Continue and create duplicate intentionally
This prevents silent structural duplication.

5️⃣ STEP 2 — Select Exam Type
Exam Type determines:
    • Marking scheme
    • Default timing windows
    • Default section structure
    • Difficulty timing mapping
No manual marks entry allowed for JEE/NEET.
All stored in template snapshot.

6️⃣ STEP 3 — Set Duration
Admin sets totalDuration.
System computes:
If L2:
